reviews.review_text: - Smokin first set, ok second. Too bad there are no really good AUDs of this, but this is a nice board.

Seventeenth Days Between 17/41: Eyes (16:48)->Drumz (28:06)->The Last Time (5:55)->Days Between (11:26)->Throwing Stones. 

The first set is surprisingly better than the second. Save for the Broken Arrow, that I just can't stomach, I really liked it. Weir gives us a strong Stranger opener, a gritty The Same Thing, and a (definitely-not-cheesy) Easy Answers. Garcia gives us a sweet MIDI'fied Ramble On Rose jam, a present BEW, and a Half-Step (!) closer. As for the second set, LSD opener is cool... but then it's all downhill and tumbling fast from there. Hummingbird Eyes... the drumz is great... then it's the first Days Between I've heard, up to now, where the singing man sounds lost, at least lyrically. What's missing, though, in terms of lyrical presence is made up for in the eerie exit-jam. First time I've heard it beginning to stretch.
